截至目前，巴西确诊拉丁美洲首例新冠肺炎病例。
So far, Brazil has confirmed the first case of new crown pneumonia in Latin America.
疫情正在从意大利向国外蔓延，周边邻国瑞士、奥地利相继出现首例确诊病例，西班牙新增一例确诊病例，确诊患者均与意大利有关。
The epidemic is spreading from Italy to abroad, with the first confirmed cases in neighboring Switzerland and Austria, and a new confirmed case in Spain, all linked to Italy.
截至25日，中东有新冠肺炎确诊病例的国家已增至9个：伊朗(95例)、巴林(17例)、阿联酋(13例)、科威特(8例)、以色列(6例)、伊拉克(5例)、阿曼(4例)、阿富汗(1例)、黎巴嫩(1例)。
As at 25, the number of confirmed cases of new crown pneumonia in the Middle East had increased to 9: Iran (95), Bahrain (17), the United Arab Emirates (13), Kuwait (8), Israel (6), Iraq (5), Oman (4), Afghanistan (1) and Lebanon (1).
该地区医疗水平和疫情控制能力参差不一，尤其是与伊朗相邻的一些国家尚处于战乱之中，伴随伊朗的输入型病例向周边蔓延，中东的疫情防控形势不容乐观。
Medical standards and disease control capabilities in the region remain uneven, particularly in countries bordering Iran, where outbreaks of disease are under control as imported cases spread to neighbouring countries.
随着疫情蔓延到30多个国家，全球恐慌情绪上升。
As the epidemic spread to more than 30 countries, global panic rose.
拉美国家首例！男子从意大利返回巴西后确诊新冠肺炎据英国《卫报》报道，巴西2月25日出现首例新冠病毒核酸检测阳性病例，巴西官方消息称，这是一名近日从意大利回到巴西圣保罗市的61岁男子。
Brazil's first case of New Crown Virus Nucleotide positive came on Feb. 25 in Brazil, according to the Guardian, a 61-year-old man who recently returned from Italy to Sao Paulo, the Guardian reported.
这名男子成为巴西首例、也是拉丁美洲首例新冠肺炎确诊病例。
The man became the first confirmed case of pneumonia in Brazil and the first in Latin America.
据报道，这名男子在2月9日至2月21日期间在意大利。
The man was reportedly in Italy from 9 February to 21 February.
他有轻微的症状，包括咳嗽。
He has mild symptoms, including a cough.
目前，这名男子在圣保罗的一家顶级医院接受治疗。
The man is being treated at a top hospital in Sao Paulo.
德国参议员：如有必要将封闭柏林德国联邦参议院参议员安德烈亚斯⋅盖塞尔25日表示，鉴于新冠肺炎病毒可能在欧洲流行，柏林可能封城或者部分封城。
German Senator: If necessary, Berlin German Federal Senate Senator Andreas Gessel said on the 25th, given that the new crown pneumonia virus may be popular in Europe, Berlin may be closed or partially closed.
盖塞尔表示，柏林已经采取了适当的民事防护措施，制定了相应的计划。
Mr Gessel said Berlin had taken appropriate civil protection measures and planned accordingly.
但如果情况危急，柏林将采取类似于意大利北部城市封城得措施。
But in case of emergency, Berlin would take measures similar to those imposed on northern Italian cities.
盖塞尔强调，至于是否封城以及在多大程度上实施如此严厉的措施尚待观察。
Mr Gessell stressed that it remained to be seen whether and to what extent such draconian measures would be imposed.
当天，德国卫生部长斯潘在罗马表示，即使意大利爆发疫情，也不应该禁止跨境旅行。
On the same day, German Health Minister Jospin said in Rome that cross-border travel should not be banned even in the event of an outbreak in Italy.
美专家称新冠病毒在美社区传播是早晚问题旧金山宣布进入紧急状态据美国有线电视新闻网（CNN）报道，当地时间2月25日，美国疾病控制和预防中心（CDC）下属国家免疫和呼吸系统疾病中心主任南希·梅索尼耶警告称，卫生专家预计新冠肺炎疫情会在美国蔓延。
SAN FRANCISCO announces state of emergency San Francisco announces state of emergency: Health experts expect the outbreak to spread in the United States, Nancy Mesonye, director of the U.S. Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) National Centre for Immunization and Respiratory Diseases, warned Monday.
报道称，梅索尼耶表示，“我们预计，我们会看到（新冠病毒）在这个国家出现社区传播。
"We expect to see community transmission [of the new crown virus] in this country," he said.
现在的问题不是这种情况会不会发生，而是究竟什么时候发生，以及这个国家将有多少人会患上严重疾病。
The question now is not whether this will happen, but when it will happen and how many people in the country will suffer from serious diseases.
”CDC也在推特上发文，美国人要为应对疫情做好准备。
The CDC also tweeted that the Americans had to be prepared for the epidemic.
“现在是美国企业、医院和社区开始为新冠肺炎可能的传播做准备的时候了。
"Now is the time for American businesses, hospitals and communities to begin preparing for the possible spread of pneumonia.
疾控中心将继续与商业、教育和医疗保健部门合作，同时提醒雇主做好准备。
CDC will continue to work with business, education and health care, while reminding employers to be prepared.
”梅索尼耶表示，其所在机构希望人们能够理解，他们的生活可能会被打乱。
Mr Messonye said his agency wanted people to understand that their lives could be disrupted.
“我们要求美国公众与我们一起做好准备。
"We ask the American public to join us in preparing.
”梅索尼耶说，“过去一周的数据，以及（新冠肺炎）在其他国家的传播情况，无疑提高了我们的担忧程度，并提高了我们对社区传播的预期水平。
"The data over the past week, and the spread of [new crown pneumonia] in other countries, have certainly raised our level of concern and our expectations of community transmission."
”截至25日，美国确诊病例已升至57例。
By the 25th, the number of confirmed cases in the United States had risen to 57.
其中，40例是从“钻石公主”号邮轮撤回的美国公民，14例为美国本土发现确诊病例，3例系从武汉撤回。
Forty of the cases were American citizens withdrawn from the cruise ship Princess Diamond. Fourteen cases were found in the United States mainland and three cases were withdrawn from Wuhan.
另据《国会山报》报道，出于对新冠肺炎疫情的担忧，旧金山市长伦敦·布里德于当地时间周二（25日）宣布该市进入紧急状态。
San Francisco Mayor London Bride declared a state of emergency Tuesday because of concerns about the outbreak of pneumonia, the Capitol Hill newspaper reported.
布里德在一份声明中说，虽然旧金山目前尚未有确诊病例，但“全球疫情形势正迅速变化，我们需要加强防范”。
Although there have been no confirmed cases in San Francisco, "the global epidemic is changing rapidly and we need to strengthen our defences," Blide said in a statement.
东京奥运会或取消？25日，曾担任过世界反兴奋剂机构前主席的迪克·庞德接受美联社采访时表示，如果新冠肺炎疫情在5月下旬得不到控制，2020年东京奥运会可能将被取消，而不是推迟或换城市举办。
TOKYO (Reuters) - Dick Pound, a former head of the World Anti-Doping Agency, said in an interview with The Associated Press yesterday that the 2020 Tokyo Olympics could be cancelled rather than postponed or exchanged for the city if the outbreak is not brought under control in late May.
对此，央视记者联系了东京奥组委进行核实。
In response, CCTV reporters contacted the Tokyo Organizing Committee for the verification.
东京奥组会对记者称，国际奥委会指出，庞德的表态说明国际奥委会正在就如期举办东京奥运会进行准备，国际奥委会多次表示奥运会的准备工作正按计划推进，为了举办安心安全的奥运会，新冠肺炎的对策十分重要。
The IOC told reporters that the IOC pointed out that Pound's statement indicated that the IOC was preparing for the Tokyo Olympic Games on schedule, that preparations for the Games were proceeding as planned and that the response to them was important in order to hold a safe and secure Olympic Games.
东京奥组委将继续关注新冠肺炎的整体情况，并与相关机构紧密联合，研究必要的对策。
TOKYO will continue to monitor the overall situation of the new crown pneumonia and work closely with relevant agencies to study necessary countermeasures.
至于3个月内（5月底前）为判断期限，这不是国际奥委会的官方见解。
It is not the official view of the IOC that the time limit should be three months (by the end of May).
据人民日报客户端消息，2月26日日本奥运担当大臣桥本圣子就此事表示，“（我们）已就此询问国际奥委会，国际奥委会回复称，‘这不是国际奥委会的官方主张，有这样的言论正说明了国际奥委会正在朝着东京奥运会按照计划举办的目标，开展准备工作。
"[We] have asked the IOC, and the IOC has responded, 'This is not an official IOC proposition, and this is an indication that the IOC is preparing for the Tokyo Olympic Games as planned," said Yasuko Hashimoto, Japan's minister for the Olympic Games on February 26.
’”关于即将于3月举行的东京奥运会火炬传递，日本官房长官菅义伟在26日的例行记者会上表示，并未从东京奥组委听到关于日程变化的消息，日本政府将与国际奥委会、东京奥组委、东京都开展紧密合作，稳步推进奥运会的准备工作。
Regarding the upcoming Tokyo Olympic Torch Relay in March, Japanese Chief Cabinet Secretary Naoto Kan said at a regular news conference on Saturday that he had heard nothing from the Tokyo Organizing Committee for the Games (TOKYO) about the change in the agenda.
安倍晋三：政府要求未来两周关键期内取消或推迟大型活动当地时间26日，日本首相安倍晋三在有关疫情的政府工作会议上表示，政府将要求大型体育和文化活动的组织者考虑在未来两周内取消或推迟有关活动，他表示，未来两周是遏制新冠肺炎病例增加的关键时期。
Shinzo Abe: Japanese Prime Minister Shinzo Abe told a government working session on the epidemic that the government will ask organizers of major sporting and cultural events to consider cancelling or postponing activities in the next two weeks, saying the next two weeks will be a critical period for curbing the rise in new crown pneumonia.
“考虑到未来一到两周对阻止病毒扩散极为重要，政府认为体育、文化活动和大规模人群聚集存在很大的传播风险。
"Given the importance of the next week or two in stopping the spread of the virus, the government sees a great risk of spreading through sports, cultural activities and mass crowds.
”日本北海道地区考虑全面停课据日本放送协会（NHK）网站25日报道，截至当地时间25日晚24时，日本全国新增新冠肺炎确诊病例11例，确诊总数达到862例。
Japan's Hokkaido region has 11 new cases of confirmed cases of pneumonia nationwide, bringing the total number of confirmed cases to 862, the Japan Hokkaido Association reported Wednesday.
其中北海道新增5例，确诊总数达到35例。
There were 5 new cases in Hokkaido, and the total number of confirmed cases reached 35.
日本新冠肺炎确诊病例分布图（NHK）北海道政府25日为此召开会议，决定要求北海道教育委员会考虑该地区所有公立学校停课，以防止感染扩大。
The government of Hokkaido (Hokkaido) decided to ask the Hokkaido Education Commission to consider closing all public schools in the region to prevent the spread of the infection.
